.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "Simple Shell Project"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIcommand\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBsimple_shell\fR is a basic UNIX command line interpreter developed as part of Holberton's Simple Shell Project. It reads user input and executes corresponding commands, replicating some behaviors of standard UNIX shells.

.SH OPTIONS
\fBsimple_shell\fR does not accept any command-line options.

.SH COMMANDS
The following built-in commands are supported:

.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH USAGE
To start the simple shell, run the following command in your terminal:

.B ./hsh

Type a command and press Enter. The shell will execute it if found in the systemâ€™s \fBPATH\fR.

